==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turkey-trot
<hw>Tur"key-trot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An eccentric
ragtime dance, danced with the feet well apart and with a characteristic
rise on the ball of the foot, followed by a drop upon the heel. The
original form, owing to the positions assumed by the dancers, is
offensively suggestive. Similar dances are the <col><b>bunny
hug</b></col> and <col><b>grizzly bear</b></col>, so called in allusion
to the movements and the positions assumed by the partners in
dancing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turkic</ent>⟦br⟧
